      "variant": "main",
      "html": "<h4>Activity</h4>\n<p>What if the point you are given isn&rsquo;t a \\(&nbsp;y&nbsp;\\)-intercept? Point-slope is a great form to use when you are given the slope and any point.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>First, work to derive the point-slope formula by completing the following steps:</p>\n<p>Start with the slope formula as&nbsp;\\( m= \\frac{y-y_1}{x-x_1} \\).</p>\n<p>Step 1: Multiply both sides of the equation by \\( x - x_1 \\).</p>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Submit\" data-content-id=\"47449637-a56f-4f2f-9f60-77c89eb8c0a9\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Check your answer:&nbsp;\\( m(x-x_1)=\\left(\\frac{y-y_1}{x-x_1}\\right)(x-x_1) \\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<p>Step 2: Simplify.</p>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Submit\" data-content-id=\"40d72c4f-b9cd-4524-9c7d-9be5dace35f8\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Check your answer:&nbsp;\\( m(x-x_1)=y-y_1 \\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<p>Step 3: Rewrite the equation with the \\(y\\) terms on the left.</p>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Submit\" data-content-id=\"d22f1f8e-c204-4d56-a9e4-50d7de126c98\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Check your answer:&nbsp;\\( y - y_1 = m(x - x_1) \\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<p>With your partner, you will find the equation of the line in point-slope form that goes through the point&nbsp;\\( (3, 4) \\) and has a slope of 2 by answering the following questions.\n  <br><br>1. Use the point and slope to graph the line on a coordinate plane.\n</p>\n<p>Write down your answer, and then select the <strong>Solution</strong> button to compare your work.</p>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"eventShow1\">\n  Sample answer:<br><img alt class=\"img-fluid atto_image_button_text-bottom\" height=\"313\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/390f352c17676b18164cb6fe769e1ef7b67d2889\" width=\"400\"><br>\n  <section data-depth=\"1\" id=\"fs-id1170654942537\">\n  </section>\n</div>\n<br>\n<p>2. Write the point-slope form.</p>\n<p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Submit\" data-content-id=\"a17e5a9f-39b8-43af-a8d6-aeb434d6e0a4\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Check your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(&nbsp;y-y_1=m(x-x_1)&nbsp;\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<p>3. Name the point \\(&nbsp;(x_1, y_1)&nbsp;\\) and the slope, \\(&nbsp;m&nbsp;\\).</p>\n<p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Submit\" data-content-id=\"3addce7a-5294-4111-ab82-ba83b95d7fbc\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Check your answer:</p>\n    <p><span>\\(&nbsp;x_1=3,\\ y_1=4,\\ m =2&nbsp;\\)</span><br></p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<p>4. Substitute the point and slope into the point-slope form.</p>\n<p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Submit\" data-content-id=\"1a5f9bf0-bc15-4f8f-b2dd-fd11545b4b2c\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Check your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(&nbsp;y -4 =2(x-3)&nbsp;\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<p>5. Now, with your partner, each solve for \\(y\\) to write the equation in slope-intercept form. Compare your answers for any possible errors. Come to an agreement on your equation. You may also choose to graph the line on a coordinate plane using a graphing calculator or Desmos with your final equation to check your answer.</p>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Submit\" data-content-id=\"24534d77-e4cd-4710-9723-978072f99fc2\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <!-- INSERT ANY VALID HTML HERE -->\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Check your answer:</p>\n    <p>\\(&nbsp;y = 2x - 2&nbsp;\\)</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<br>"
